label.value: B220-low CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell

value.value: A B220-low CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell is a CD38-positive unswitched memory B cell that has the phenotype B220-low, CD38-positive, IgD-positive, CD138-negative, and IgG-negative.

label.value: IgG-negative class switched memory B cell

value.value: A class switched memory B cell that lacks IgG on the cell surface.

label.value: CD38-negative IgG-negative class switched memory B cell

value.value: A CD38-negative IgG-negative memory B cell is a IgG-negative class switched memory B cell that lacks IgG on the cell surface with the phenotype CD38-negative and IgG-negative.

label.value: CD38-positive IgG-negative class switched memory B cell

value.value: A CD38-positive IgG-negative memory B cell is an IgG-negative class switched memory B cell that lacks IgG on the cell surface with the phenotype CD38-positive and IgG-negative.

label.value: CD24-positive CD38-negative IgG-negative class switched memory B cell

value.value: An CD24-positive CD38-negative IgG-negative memory B cell is a CD38-negative IgG-negative class switched memory B cell that lacks IgG on the cell surface with the phenotype CD24-positive, CD38-negative, and IgG-negative.

label.value: CD24-negative CD38-negative IgG-negative class switched memory B cell

value.value: A CD24-negative CD38-negative IgG-negative memory B cell is a CD38-negative IgG-negative class switched memory B cell that lacks IgG on the cell surface with the phenotype CD24-negative, CD38-negative, and IgG-negative.

label.value: B220-positive CD38-positive IgG-negative class switched memory B cell

value.value: A B220-positive CD38-positive IgG-negative memory B cell is a CD38-positive IgG-negative class switched memory B cell that lacks IgG on the cell surface with the phenotype B220-positive, CD38-positive, and IgG-negative.

label.value: B220-low CD38-positive IgG-negative class switched memory B cell

value.value: A B220-low CD38-positive IgG-negative memory B cell is a CD38-positive IgG-negative class switched memory B cell that lacks IgG on the cell surface with the phenotype B220-low, CD38-positive, and IgG-positive.
A circulating gamma-delta T cell that is CD27-positive and capable of producing IFN-gamma.

label.value: CD25-positive, CD27-positive immature gamma-delta T cell

value.value: A CD25-positive, CD27-positive immature gamma-delta T cell found in the thymus that has an immature phenotype (i.e. CD24-high, CD25-high, CD62L-high, CD44-high, CD2-low, CD5-low).
A T cell with a receptor of limited diversity that is capable of immediate effector functions upon stimulation.
A stomal cell of the ovary
A stromal cell of the ovarian medulla.

A endothelial cell of a lymphatic vessel. The border of the oak leaf-shaped endothelial cell of initial lymphatics are joined by specialized buttons. The discontinuous feature of buttons distinguishes them from zippers in collecting lymphatics, but both types of junctions are composed of proteins typical of adherens junctions and tight junctions found in the endothelium of blood vessels. Buttons seal the sides of flaps of the oak leaf-shaped endothelial cell, leaving open the tips of flaps as routes for fluid entry without disassembly and reformation of intercellular junctions.
An endothelial cell of the vascular tree, which includes blood vessels and lymphatic vessels.

definition.value: These cells are reportedly CD31-positive, CD34-positive, CD144-positive, TAL1-positive.

value.value: A sebum secreting cell of the skin that secretes sebum into the hair follicles.
An endothelial cell found in capillaries.

label.value: ciliated columnar cell of tracheobronchial tree

value.value: A ciliated columnar cell found in the trachea and bronchus. Vary from low to tall columnar; possesses up to 300 cilia at its surface, interspersed with long irregular microvilli with the cilia varying in length from about 6um in the trachea to about 4um in the terminal bronchioles; driving force of the ciliary current in the bronchial tree.
A cell found within the dental pulp.
An epithelial cell of the uterus.
The dead keratin-filled squamous cell of the stratum corneum. This cell type lacks a nucleus.
Epithelial cells derived from general body ectoderm and ectoderm placodes.
An epithelial cell that remains from the disintegration of the epithelial root sheath involved in the development of teeth.
A specialized cell involved in sensory perception of smell.

label.value: keratinized cell of the oral mucosa

value.value: A keratinized cell located in the hard palate or gingiva.

label.value: folliculostellate cell of pars distalis of adenohypophysis

value.value: A supporting cell of the anterior pituitary gland involved in trophic and catabolic processes; expresses a broad spectrum of cytokeratins indicative of their epithelial nature.
An epithelial cell found in the lining of the stomach.
A mucous cell in the epithelium of the stomach.

A stomach epithelial cell that is olumnar in form with a few short apical microvilli; relatively undifferentiated mitotic cell from which other types of gland are derived; few in number, situated in the isthmus region of the gland and base of the gastric pit.
A basally situated, mitotically active, columnar-shaped keratinocyte attached to the basement membrane.
An endothelial cell found in the glomerulus of the kidney. This cell is flattened, highly fenestrated, and plays a vital role in the formation of glomerular ultrafiltrate.
A cell involved in the formation of a granulocyte.
A cell involved in the formation of a monocyte (monopoiesis).

A stem cell that can give rise to the cells of the liver. The term usually refers to the self-renewing pool of hepatocyte precursors in the adult liver (differently from 'hepatoblast', often used for fetal precursors of hepatocytes).

A large epithelial cell with an extremely acidophilic and granular cytoplasm, containing vast numbers of mitochondria; such cells may undergo neoplastic transformation. From the Greek word onkos meaning swelling, this cell type is found in parathyroid, salivary and thyroid glands.
An oncocyte located in the parathyroid gland.
An oncocyte located in the thyroid.
An epithelial cell of the tracheobronchial tree.
An epithelial cell present in the trachea and bronchi; columnar in shape; generally lack cilia; immature forms of ciliated or secretory cells which have been formed from stem cells.

label.value: immature dendritic epithelial T cell precursor

value.value: A double negative thymocyte that has a T cell receptor consisting of a gamma chain that has as part a Vgamma3 segment, and a delta chain. This cell type is CD4-negative, CD8-negative and CD24-positive. This cell-type is found in the fetal thymus with highest numbers occurring at E17-E18.

definition.value: NOTE: currently variable immune gene segments are not represented in the OBO Foundry. Cross-product definitions were not made as a result. Also, there are three different nomenclatures for the variable gamma segments.

value.value: A cell located between the pinealocytes.
A cell comprising the transparent, biconvex body separating the posterior chamber and vitreous body, and constituting part of the refracting mechanism of the mammalian eye.

A cell of the cuboidal epithelium that covers the lens. The cells of the lens epithelium regulate most of the homeostatic functions of the lens. As ions, nutrients, and liquid enter the lens from the aqueous humor, Na+/K+ ATPase pumps in the lens epithelial cells pump ions out of the lens to maintain appropriate lens osmolarity and volume, with equatorially positioned lens epithelium cells contributing most to this current. The activity of the Na+/K+ ATPases keeps water and current flowing through the lens from the poles and exiting through the equatorial regions. The cells of the lens epithelium also serve as the progenitors for new lens fibers. It constantly lays down fibers in the embryo, fetus, infant, and adult, and continues to lay down fibers for lifelong growth.
An epithelial cell of the prostate.
An epithelial cell of prostatic duct.

label.value: basal epithelial cell of prostatic duct

value.value: A cell that constitutes the basal layer of epithelium in the prostatic duct.
A fibroblast in the bone marrow.
A fibroblasts found in interstitial spaces in the pulmonary tract. Greater numbers of these cells are found in idiopathic pulmonary fibrosis.
A cell containing at least one nucleus.

label.value: smooth muscle cell of sphincter of pupil

value.value: A circular smooth muscle cell of the iris, innervated by the ciliary nerves (parasympathetic), and acting to contract the pupil. This muscle cell derives from neuroectoderm. This smooth muscle cell results from transformation of epithelial cells to smooth muscle cells.
